            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-109" n="109">Hear one Story more, and then I will Stop:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-110" n="110">I Dreamt Wood was told He should dye by a Drop:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-111" n="111"><lb/>So methought, He resolved no Liquor to Tast,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-112" n="112">For fear the first Drop might as well be his Last:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-113" n="113"><lb/>But Dreams are like Oracles, 'tis hard to explain 'em,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-114" n="114">For it prov'd that He dy'd of a Drop at <note place="foot">·Their Place of Execution.</note> Kilmainham:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-115" n="115"><lb/>I wak'd with Delight, and not without Hope</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-116" n="116">Very soon to see Wood Drop down from a Rope.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-117" n="117"><lb/>How He, and how we at each other should Grin!</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-118" n="118">Tis Kindness to hold a Friend up by the Chin.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-119" n="119"><lb/>But Soft says the Herauld, I cannot agree:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-120" n="120">For Metal on Metal is false Heraldry:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-121" n="121"><lb/>Why that may be true, yet WOOD upon WOOD,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-265Y-line-122" n="122">Ile maintain with my Life is Heraldry good.</l>
          </lg>
